node.text:
Happening tomorrow, a very special Sofar co-curated by Full Circle: First Nations Performance. In celebration of Indigenous History Month, we've brought together 3 remarkable artists to share their talents, voice and passion for community. 

Full Circle: First Nations Performance is a non-profit society and registered charity that creates opportunities for Indigenous artists. Margo Kane (Cree/Saulteaux), an interdisciplinary artist and Indigenous arts leader, founded Full Circle in 1992. Upon establishing Full Circle, Kane’s vision was to make a profound contribution to the development of Indigenous performance in Canada.

Traditionally, in the Indigenous world, art is not separated from the community. It is integral to a happy and healthy way of life. We share Full Circle's belief in rooting art back into the community, and hope you'll join us tomorrow night! 

Thu, Jun 29 📍 Little Mountain ~ 7:30pm 

Save & Share with a Friend
🎟️ Ticket info available at the link in our bio.

#SofarVancouver #LiveMusic #Concert #Vancouver #Music #Events #LocalMusic #VancouverMusic #SofarSounds

node.text:
Dreaming of a space by bluer waters? ✨ Aloha from Island Sound Studios, an iconic recording studio on the water in Honolulu, HI. This 10,000 square foot space has captured recordings from iconic stars like Beyonce, Justin Bieber, Drake, Snoop Dogg, to name a few. Now, under a new name and new ownership, it’s bringing a wealth of music into the world through global artists and a strong local community. 

Hit the link in bio to see co-owners Bryan Spicer and Kyle Spicer and Sofar Curator Michelle Anderson guide us through this scenic recording studio, and show us how the space transforms into a dynamic live performance room. 

📍 @islandsoundstudios 
📍 @sofarhonolulu

#SofarSounds #IslandSoundStudios #ThisMustBeTheSpace

node.text:
In celebration of this year’s Asian American Pacific Islander Heritage Month 2023, we’re sharing incredible performances from Asian American and Pacific Islander artists in the Sofar community. Head to our Spotify or YouTube channels to find curated playlists, celebrating both new releases and vintage favorites from artists we love. 

Hear's a taste of what you can find on our Asian American & Pacific Islander Voices playlist. Discover more music through the link in our bio and stay tuned for in-person show announcements coming soon! 

🎤 @anusha.savi 
🎤 @just_an_egg 
🎤 @gisunmusic 
🎤 @basivibe 
🎤 @hien999 

#SofarSounds #AAPIHeritageMonth

Forget about the traditional couples' celebration and let's gather together with the one's who will ALWAYS be there for you! ✨ YOUR FRIENDS ✨ They're the family we choose and what better way to create new memories together than at a Sofar. 

Join us Monday, Feb. 13th in Mount Pleasant for our Pal-entine's Show dedicated to you and your ride-or-dies'. 

Mon, Feb 13th 📍 Mount Pleasant
🎟️ Ticket info available at the link in our bio.

#SofarVancouver #LiveMusic #ValentinesDay #Concert #Vancouver #Music #Events #VancouverMusic #SofarSounds

See @xjaelunax's dish come together at the link in bio.

node.text:
Listening to @itsunamey’s enchanting tunes and unique vocals at @fabriquestgeorge felt like a DREAM! 😍Juxtaposing bright instrumentals with introspective, melancholic lyrics, Una Mey creates a powerful listening experience that draws you in through her raw emotion and gets you in your feelings.✨

We had the opportunity to hear some of the beautiful unreleased music Una has been working on that you definitely don’t wanna miss out on, so be sure to give her a follow so you can be the first to know when she is performing next / releasing new tunes! 

#SofarVancouver #LiveMusic #Concert #Vancouver #Music #Events #LocalMusic #VancouverMusic #SofarSounds

node.text:
Home to unique shops, art galleries, cafés, restaurants, and more, we LOVE the  vibrancy of the North Shore, and the views we get of the city skyline in the Shipyards District are some of the best! 😍🚢✨ 

This Saturday’s show is taking us to the Shipyards Brewery District so get ready for some incredible brews and views! 👀🍻

Whether you’re in the area or you’d like an excuse to come explore this gorgeous neighbourhood, grab yourself some tickets and join us for a night of live music! 🤗🎶

Sat, Nov 11 📍 North Vancouver ~ Local Brewery!

Save and Share with a Friend.
🎟️ Ticket info available at the link in our bio.

node.text:
The energy @sade_awele brings to a room when she gets on stage is absolutely MAGICAL! 🤩🙌

Channelling her Nigerian heritage into innovative Afro-Soul and R&B sounds, Sadé creates a bold, genre-bending style of her own and together with her bandmates @kaitieslymusic and @aminoacid.13, they form the band “Serengeti.” ✨

This group has just released their newest single “Muse Baby” which we had the honour of hearing in this intimate live performance and it was a VIBE! 🥳

If you’d like to groove along to this song and more like it, check out Sadé and Serengeti wherever you stream music, and follow them to stay up to date with new releases and upcoming shows! 🫶

📍@herschelvancouver / @herschelsupply

node.text:
There is nothing quite like the feeling of warmth and connectedness that live music can bring to a room, and this performance by @brendanscottfriel at @sincerely.studio did just that! 🥰 Visiting from Windsor, Ontario, Brendan captivated us with his pure vocals and vulnerable storytelling, and his enthusiasm on stage was truly infectious! ❤️

One of our favourite moments was this impromptu performance of his song “Simon the Doubter” from his latest album titled “2021” which just released earlier this month! 🙌

Thank you Brendan for coming to visit us on the West Coast and sharing such a memorable night with us all! 🥹🫶

node.text:
Immersing us in calming soundscapes, @neighborhood.libraries shared this beautiful performance with us for our World Mental Health Day show with @twloha and @nettwerkmusic. 🥰

In transitioning from a musician’s life of travel to the solitude of lockdown, Neighborhood Libraries was inspired to create a series of wordless sonic journeys that, through ambient-electronic, piano-driven melody, take the listener through a spectrum of emotion. 

We got to to experience his EP “Postcards for the Backyard” which centres around finding beauty in the immediate, and we loved how it truly grounded us in the present moment. ❤️

You can listen to this EP along with more of Neighborhood Libraries’ stunning projects on all streaming platforms! 🫶✨

📍@northpointbrewing

Last week we had the opportunity to enjoy a Night of Music and Healing in support of World Mental Health Day with @nettwerkmusic and @twloha. 🌎❤️

We are incredibly blessed to be able to create space within our community to encourage healing through music and storytelling, and share moments like this together.❤️ 

Thank you to @leodejohnson, @neighborhood.libraries, & @gerttabernermusic for your beautiful performances and vulnerability! 🫶

Thank you @northpointbrewing for hosting us! 

#WorldMentalHealthDay #SofarSounds #NettwerkMusic #TWLOHA #MentalHealthAwareness
